            <div class="st-card">
              <h4>Founder / CEO / leadership</h4>
              <span class="st-tag">Pain</span>
              <p>Strategy is scattered; board narrative is hard to prepare; alignment is weak; decisions aren't remembered; people and agents work from different assumptions.</p>
              <span class="st-tag h">Message</span>
              <p>Orient gives leadership one place to know what the company knows, resolve what it does not, and communicate what matters.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="st-card">
              <h4>Chief Product Officer</h4>
              <span class="st-tag">Pain</span>
              <p>Roadmap decisions lack visible reasoning; product, sales, support, and marketing drift apart; feedback is scattered; narratives go stale.</p>
              <span class="st-tag h">Message</span>
              <p>Orient turns product knowledge into decisions, launch frames, enablement, and machine-ready context.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="st-card">
              <h4>Head of Strategy / Chief of Staff</h4>
              <span class="st-tag">Pain</span>
              <p>Complex work lives across meetings, docs, decks, and Slack; strategic questions stay unresolved; leaders need better briefings and follow-through.</p>
              <span class="st-tag h">Message</span>
              <p>Orient is the workspace for turning strategic uncertainty into shared answers and action.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="st-card">
              <h4>Head of Sales / Revenue</h4>
              <span class="st-tag">Pain</span>
              <p>Sales claims become inconsistent; old decks circulate; reps improvise positioning; agents need approved context.</p>
              <span class="st-tag h">Message</span>
              <p>Orient keeps sales teams and sales agents working from current positioning, proof points, objections, and approved claims.</p>
