          <div class="st-cards">
            <div class="st-card">
              <h4>Orient for Humans</h4>
              <p>For teams who need to think, decide, frame, and remember. Capture, Resolve, Frame, Ask, Answers, Frames library, Deep Reads, Topics, People, Impact, Library, Memos.</p>
              <span class="st-tag h">Pricing</span>
              <p><b>From $36 / month / full user. Viewers free.</b></p>
              <p>Pay for the people doing the thinking. Make viewing free so understanding can spread.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="st-card">
              <h4>Orient for Machines</h4>
              <p>For companies deploying agents, copilots, workflows, and AI that need organisational meaning. Meaning API, context assembly, resolver access, machine-readable frames, memory graph, topic/people/comprehension intelligence, permissions, audit, safe-to-act signals, meaning integrity evaluation.</p>
              <span class="st-tag m">Pricing</span>
              <p>Platform fee · machine consumer fee · meaning consumption. <b>Machines are priced by dependency.</b></p>
            </div>
            <div class="st-card">
              <h4>Combined Human + Machine</h4>
              <p>The strategic account: human thinking workspace, machine-ready meaning layer, agent access, governed context, evaluation, and expansion across teams.</p>
              <span class="st-tag">Core line</span>
              <p><b>Humans create the meaning layer. Machines consume it.</b></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

