          <span class="sec-eyebrow">12 · Year-one GTM plan</span>
          <h2>Prove Orient can become strategic inside a few serious organisations.</h2>
          <p>The objective is not maximum user count. Targets: <b>$1m ARR</b> base · <b>$2m ARR</b> internal · <b>$5m ARR</b> hero — from <b>10–20 serious companies</b>, not many low-value accounts.</p>
          <span class="st-tag">Customer mix</span>
          <ul>
            <li>3–5 AI-native / software companies; 2–4 product-led companies;</li>
            <li>2–3 consulting or advisory firms; 2–3 research-heavy or deep tech orgs;</li>
            <li>1–3 larger strategic accounts; 2–4 companies deploying internal agents.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="st-steps">
            <div class="st-step"><div class="si">P1</div><div><h4>Founder-led design partners</h4><p>5–8 design partners across board prep, AI strategy, product launch, sales positioning, research synthesis, agent context. Success: real material used, ≥1 resolved answer, ≥1 frame, multiple viewers, a second workspace identified, machine-layer interest validated.</p></div></div>
            <div class="st-step"><div class="si">P2</div><div><h4>Paid team deployments</h4><p>5–10 paid customers at $50k–$100k ARR; repeated Resolve and Frame use; viewers spreading work; machine-layer pilots beginning.</p></div></div>
            <div class="st-step"><div class="si">P3</div><div><h4>Machine access pilots</h4><p>3–5 pilots: agent grounding, approved claim retrieval, sales agent context, support escalation, research work queues, executive briefing agents. Success: agents consume context, outputs improve, unsupported claims drop, safe-to-act signal is valuable, customer accepts machine pricing.</p></div></div>
            <div class="st-step"><div class="si">P4</div><div><h4>Strategic account expansion</h4><p>2–4 larger accounts at $200k+ ARR with executive sponsorship; machine access becomes part of AI strategy; Orient becomes part of the operating rhythm.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </section>

