        <!-- 21 -->
        <section id="summary-end">
          <span class="sec-eyebrow">21 · Summary</span>
          <h2>Focused, strategic, and expansion-led.</h2>
          <p>Land first where important teams need to think clearly: strategy, product, sales, research, board prep, and agent readiness. Sell a concrete human outcome — <b>turn scattered knowledge into trusted answers and frames</b> — then expand into the machine layer: <b>give agents and workflows the organisation's resolved meaning, context, memory, and safe-to-act signals.</b></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Humans create the meaning graph through real work.</li>
            <li>Machines consume that graph to act safely.</li>
            <li>Orient becomes more valuable as both sides use it.</li>
            <li>The account expands from seats to infrastructure.</li>
            <li>The category becomes a shared meaning system for human and machine work.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="st-line">Orient is the shared meaning layer for people and AI. Humans feed the graph. Machines act from it. Orient keeps both working from the same understanding.</div>
